data.title: William Faulkne Biography
data.meta_description: William Faulkne Biography - Free download as Word Doc (.doc / .docx), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. The document provides biographical details about renowned American author William Faulkner. It describes how he was born in Mississippi to a family with a history of success, but he struggled academically as a youth. After a brief stint in the Royal Air Force following World War I, he began writing poems and stories. He published his first novel in 1926 but struggled financially for many years as he developed his style writing about the fictional Yoknapatawpha County in Mississippi, the setting for many of his greatest works.
